{{One source|date=April 2010}} {{Infobox person | name = Edith Borella | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = {{Death date|1974|3|6}} | death_place = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], [[United States|U.S.]] | restingplace = | restingplacecoordinates = | othername = | occupation = [[Actress]] | yearsactive = | spouse = [[Edward Coxen]] (1914–1974; her death) | partner = | children = }}
'''Edith Borella''' (died March 6, 1974) was an [[United States|American]] [[silent film]] [[actress]] of [[Swiss people|Swiss]] descent. She starred in films such as the 1913 film ''[[Through the Neighbor's Window]]'' with [[Charlotte Burton]] which was her debut. Her career only lasted two years between 1913 and 1915 but in that period of time she starred in 46 films. She married popular English-American actor [[Edward Coxen]] in 1914.
==Selected filmography== * ''[[Through the Neighbor's Window]]'' (1913) * ''[[The Shriner's Daughter]]'' (1913) * ''[[The Power of Light]]'' (1914) * ''[[A Blowout at Santa Banana]]'' (1914) * ''[[The Widow's Investment]]'' (1914) * ''[[The Story of the Olive]]'' (1914) * ''[[Calamity Anne's Love Affair]]'' (1914) * ''[[A Soul Astray]]'' (1914) * ''[[Mein Lieber Katrina Catches a Convict]]'' (1914) * ''[[The Lure of the Sawdust]]'' (1914) * ''[[The Butterfly (1914 film)|The Butterfly]]'' (1914) * ''[[Their Worldly Goods]]'' (1914) * ''[[This Is th' Life]]'' (1914) * ''[[The Song of the Sea Shell]]'' (1914) * ''[[The Wrong Birds]]'' (1914) * ''[[The Redemption of a Pal]]'' (1914) * ''[[A Slice of Life (1914 film)|A Slice of Life]]'' (1914) * ''[[The Strength o' Ten]]'' (1914) * ''[[The Unseen Vengeance]]'' (1914) * ''[[In the Sunlight]]'' (1915)
