{{EngvarB|date=August 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox rugby league biography |name = Jack Baker |fullname = Reuben John Baker |image = |caption = |position = {{rlp|SR}} |birth_date = 1890 |birth_place = [[Picton, New South Wales|Picton]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]] |death_date = 1947 |death_place = [[North Sydney, New South Wales|North Sydney]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]] |height = |weight = |club1 = [[South Sydney Rabbitohs|South Sydney]] |year1start = 1919 |year1end = 20 |appearances1 = 24 |tries1 = 5 |goals1 = 0 |fieldgoals1 = 0 |points1 = 15 |club2 = [[North Sydney Bears|North Sydney]] |year2start = 1921 |year2end = 23 |appearances2 = 32 |tries2 = 3 |goals2 = 0 |fieldgoals2 = 0 |points2 = 9 |source = <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/players/jack-baker/summary.html|title=Jack Baker - Career Stats & Summary - Rugby League Project|first=Shawn Dollin and Andrew|last=Ferguson|website=Rugbyleagueproject.org|accessdate=22 June 2018}}</ref> }}
'''Jack Baker''' (1890 – 1947) was an Australian [[rugby league]] footballer of the 1910s and 1920s. He played in the [[NSWRFL premiership]] for the [[North Sydney Bears|North Sydney]] and [[South Sydney Rabbitohs|South Sydney]] clubs. His position was at second-row. Baker was a member of Norths only premiership victories in 1921 and 1922. He played in the 1922 grand final against Glebe where Norths won 35-3 at The [[Sydney Cricket Ground]]. After retirement, Baker worked as a police sergeant.
Baker died while living at North Sydney in 1947.<ref>[https://www.northsydneybears.com.au/happy110/] {{dead link|date=June 2018}}</ref>
